As it turns out 10K years in the cave of wonders wasn't in the cards.  Spoilers ahead... why aren't Aladdin and Jasmine married yet? That lost this movie one star.  However who would have thought that a bird could kill a djinn?  I guess the people at Disney did.  I will definitely watch this again.  (I have a kid)
Loved this movie since I was a kid.

My kids, my husband and I all love the Aladdin series. I do wish genie in this movie was Robin Williams' voice, but regardless, it is a great movie and my kids are glued anytime we put it on. Now that we have it on our Amazon videos, they can watch it anytime.

Is this more fun than the original Alladin movie? I don't know, maybe.

The gang is all here, Jafar is back, and more evil than ever. He's got plots and schemes and our intrepid heroes manage to save the day. Iago is really fun in this film. Robin Williams didn't voice the genie in this one, but Dan Castallaneta does a pretty good version.

For a straight to video movie, this one was really really fun as a kid. I don't know how many times we watched this.
I was so excited to add this to our movie collection! The film is high quality and plays perfectly. I'm so glad Amazon offers these films! I can't wait to get the 3rd Aladdin.

It was no Aladdin - tough to do a movie like this without Robin Williams.

Ah The Return of Jafar. Growing up watching Disney movies, I didn't care about sequels and prequels and all the extra that came with a fictional or nonfictional lore of media. I just watched to enjoy and occupy my curious child mind. When I was younger, I enjoyed every second of the Aladdin sequel. Today, I still enjoy it just as much as I did, the catchy tune, the proper voice actors. With that being said, the art direction and animation didn't age well at all. I never noticed but it looks terrible. Overall I enjoyed myself again and it was a great look back at my younger years. Thanks Aladdin.

Aladdin, the original movie, was very good. This one, not so much. The animation was sub par if not really bad in parts. Usually, Disney movies are a pretty good bet for young kids, and I can enjoy watching them, but this one just isn't up to their standards.
I like the other two Aladin movies better this has always been second rate to those, everything including the music is third rate.

As an 80s baby, I had found memories of this growing up.  After my daughter started liking Aladdin I got her this.  She loves it.  But with the Genie not Robin Williams and the lower budget drawing it was less of a quality movie as I remember.

But the stories was still good, and my daughter loves it.  It also breaks up the same songs she wants to hear from Aladdin.  So that was a plus.
